<para id="fs-idm277092944"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67921"/>What information do you need to calculate the weighted average common shares outstanding?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm283643712">
<problem id="fs-idm283643456">
<para id="fs-idm280618160"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67921"/>Which is the only ratio required to be reported on the face of a company’s financial statements? What are the two ways the ratio is required to be reported?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm277226672">
<para id="fs-idm277226416">EPS is the only ratio required by GAAP to be reported on the face of the income statement. It must be reported in two ways: basic and diluted (if applicable).</para>
</solution>
